{"questionId":"9506","questionHtml":"<p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = \\frac{1}{{1 - {x^2}}}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 1 < x < 1\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;Use partial fractions to find&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int {f\\left( x \\right)} {\\text{ }}dx\">\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{1 - {x^2}}} = \\frac{1}{{\\left( {1 - x} \\right)\\left( {1 + x} \\right)}} \\equiv \\frac{A}{{1 - x}} + \\frac{B}{{1 + x}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>≡</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>A</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>B</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow 1 \\equiv A\\left( {1 + x} \\right) + B\\left( {1 - x} \\right) \\Rightarrow A = B = \\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>≡</mo>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;M1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int {\\frac{{\\tfrac{1}{2}}}{{1 - x}}}&nbsp; + \\frac{{\\tfrac{1}{2}}}{{1 + x}}dx = \\frac{{ - 1}}{2}\\ln \\left( {1 - x} \\right) + \\frac{1}{2}\\ln \\left( {1 + x} \\right) + c\">\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>ln</mi>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>ln</mi>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( { = \\ln k\\sqrt {\\frac{{1 + x}}{{1 - x}}} } \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mi>ln</mi>\n      <mo>⁡</mo>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mfrac>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[8 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9506","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.1","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Let f ( x ) = 1 1 − x 2 for − 1 < x < 1 . Use partial fractions to find ∫ f ( x ) d x .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"1","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 8]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.11—Partial fractions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}